metadata.name: Jet A-Jet A-1
alternate_names: Aviation Turbine Fuel (Kerosene Type), Turbo Fuel A/Turbo Fuel A-1; Carburant pour turbine aviation (type kérosène), carburant turbo A / carburant turbo A-1

reference.reference: Harris, G., The Comparative Toxicity of Crude and Refined Oils to Daphnia Magna, Environment Canada Manuscript Report Number EE-152, Ottawa, Ontario, 29 pp., 1992

metadata.comments: A petroleum distillate blended from kerosene fractions and used in civil aviation.  Jet A-1, the  operational fuel for all turboprop and turbojet aircraft requiring a low freezing point product, is similar to Jet A except for a lower freezing point_x000D_. For additional fuel specifications refer to ASTM D1655
